Wash and dry all produce. Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a simmer. Halve, peel, and thinly slice the @yellow onion{1}. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Finely chop the @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Thinly slice the @green olives{1%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Season the @shrimp{10%ounce} with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the shrimp to the pan and cook, tossing for ~{1-2%minutes}, until almost cooked through. Remove from the pan and set aside.

Add the @Israeli couscous{3/4%cup} to the boiling water and cook for ~{8-10%minutes}, until al dente. Drain.

== Marinara Sauce ==

Make the marinara sauce: Heat another drizzle of olive oil in the same pan over medium heat. Add the garlic, onion, and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} (to taste) and cook, tossing for ~{4-5%minutes}, until softened. Add the @crushed tomatoes{1%box} and olives and simmer for ~{5%minutes}. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Stir the shrimp and half the parsley into the sauce and cook for ~{1-2%minutes}, until the shrimp are opaque. Season to taste with salt, pepper, and chili flakes, if desired.

Plate and serve: Serve the shrimp saganaki on a bed of Israeli couscous, garnish with the @Feta cheese{1/2%cup} and remaining parsley. Enjoy!